1. In column K (helper) we will count unticked rows up to each row: =IF(Ir<>"ü",COUNTIF($I$2:Ir,"<>ü"),"")
2. In column J (output) we will retrieve the nth unticked branch using INDEX/MATCH: =IFERROR(INDEX($A$2:$A${max_row},MATCH(ROW()-ROW($J$2)+1,$K$2:$K${max_row},0)) ,"")
These formulas are LibreOffice‑compatible, avoid dynamic‑array functions, and will populate column J with the list of branches lacking a tick. We'll write the header labels, fill the formulas for all rows, save the workbook to the output directory, recalculate, and finally verify that column J contains the expected values.
